cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

The paper discusses the coexistence of radar and communication networks in shared spectrum bands, which involves topics related to network interference, communication protocols, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and communication systems, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely sub-category. The study of system performance and design tradeoffs falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control), making it the third likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of interference on radar detection, which relates to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as a fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the use of mm-wave radars in the study suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a fifth likely sub-category.
